{"word":"Beth-Shemesh","slug":"beth-shemesh","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>Beth-Shemesh</b> <a href=\"#/H1053\">H1053</a> <br/> 1. A sacerdotal city of Dan<br/> - General references<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=21&verse=16'>Jos 21:16</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=6&verse=15'>1Sa 6:15</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=13&chapter=6&verse=59'>1Ch 6:59</a> <br/> - On the northern border of Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=15&verse=10'>Jos 15:10</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=6&verse=9'>1Sa 6:9</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=9&chapter=6&verse=12'>1Sa 6:12</a> <br/> - In later times transferred to Judah<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=14&verse=11'>2Ki 14:11</a> <br/> - Mentioned in Solomon's commissary districts<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=11&chapter=4&verse=9'>1Ki 4:9</a> <br/> - Amaziah taken prisoner at<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=12&chapter=14&verse=13'>2Ki 14:13</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=25&verse=23'>2Ch 25:23</a> <br/> - Retaken by the Philistines<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=14&chapter=28&verse=18'>2Ch 28:18</a> <br/> - Called Ir-Shemesh<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=19&verse=41'>Jos 19:41</a> <br/> 2. A city near Jerusalem<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=19&verse=22'>Jos 19:22</a><br/> 3. A fortified city of Naphtali<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=6&chapter=19&verse=38'>Jos 19:38</a>; <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=7&chapter=1&verse=33'>Jdg 1:33</a><br/> 4. An idolatrous temple<br/> <a href='https://www.wordofgod.in/bibles/?book=24&chapter=43&verse=13'>Jer 43:13</a>"}]}